Introduction

Hong Eunchae is a South Korean singer-songwriter, composer, and dancer under Source Music. She is best known as the maknae of the girl group LE SSERAFIM.

Eunchae debuted as a member of LE SSERAFIM on May 2, 2022, with their first mini album "FEARLESS".

On February 3, 2023, Eunchae was announced to be the newest MC for the South Korean music show Music Bank. Her first show as an MC took place on February 10. On September 12, 2024, it was announced Eunchae would be stepping down from her role as MC of Music Bank after a year and a half. Her final show as MC took place on September 28.
